      <h3>2. Streaming and Simulcasting Changed Everything</h3>
      <p>Thanks to services like **Crunchyroll**, **Netflix**, **Funimation**, and **Disney+**, anime is accessible globally within hours of release in Japan. Simulcasts ensure fans from Nairobi to New York can experience new episodes together. This has created a more connected, real-time fanbase.</p>

      <h3>3. The Rise of AI-Enhanced Anime Production</h3>
      <p>Studios are now using AI to enhance animation workflows. Backgrounds, frame in-betweens, and even voice pre-rendering have been optimized with tech. While traditional artists still lead creatively, AI is helping speed up timelines‚Äîallowing more seasonal content and higher quality visuals.</p>

      <h3>4. Community: Cosplay, Conventions, and Content Creators</h3>
      <p>In 2025, anime is as much about the fans as the shows. Cosplayers create film-level outfits. YouTubers break down episodes in real-time. TikTok trends are filled with anime edits, dances, and memes. Anime conventions now fill stadiums, not just hotel ballrooms.</p>

      <h3>5. Top Anime Leading the Charge in 2025</h3>
      <p>These are the most talked-about and beloved anime in the current year:</p>
      <ul>
